description:
&lt;p&gt;AMHP Lead Band 7 - Full Time and Part time available&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen to be the Band 7 AMHP Lead for Luton and Bedfordshire AMHP Service. You will be responsible for providing operational management and leadership to a team of AMHPs and junior staff, ensuring the smooth and efficient running of the team. Offering expertise to multidisciplinary colleagues to ensure the timely delivery of a safe, effective, responsive and well led AMHP Service that is caring and maximizes peoples statutory rights. This is an exciting time to be part of the AMHP Service, as we are due to be a pilot site for the national AMHP standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to work closely with the AMHP Operational Manager to develop both AMHP Service teams across the county; ensuring that the achievement of best quality and performance standards are met, in line with service user and carer expectations, commissioner requirements and Trust objectives. This will involve consulting and liaising with all internal and external partners, and positively reinforcing the values and expectations of the organisation through collaborative and dynamic management and leadership that is both supportive and encouraging in nature to enable the team to adapt to key changes smoothly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to take a lead role in the development of the overall AMHP Service in Luton and Bedfordshire, which aims to ensure the service, is fit for purpose for the next ten years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The AMHP Service currently operates Monday to Friday 09.00-17.00hrs. You will need to be a car driver, with the flexibility to travel across the county and to be able to cover the needs of both teams, when required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Beatrice Tinkler, telephone 07801826578, email beatrice.tinkler@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
